# HMI Dashboard Design

A graphical dashboard was created to represent the simulated tank control system.

### Dashboard Components

| Component            | Function                         |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Tank Level Indicator | Displays water level in tank     |
| Pump Control Buttons | Start and stop pump              |
| Alarm Indicator      | Shows high-level alarm condition |
| Numeric Display      | Displays sensor value            |

These components provide a visual representation of the industrial process.

---

# PLC–SCADA Communication

Communication between SCADA and the PLC occurs through **Modbus TCP**, allowing the SCADA system to read and write values from the PLC registers.

### Modbus Tag Mapping

| Tag Name     | Modbus Address     | Function                       |
| ------------ | ------------------ | ------------------------------ |
| Tank_Level   | Holding Register 0 | Displays tank level            |
| Pump_Control | Coil 1             | Controls pump operation        |
| High_Alarm   | Coil 3             | Indicates high-level condition |

This mapping allows the SCADA dashboard to interact directly with the PLC.

